    <text type="petition">
        <body>            
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01077.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">

                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">                    
                        <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk &amp;c.</salute>
                        <salute>Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <p><persName>Jesse D. Bright</persName> of <placeName>Indiana</placeName> having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned and, having refused or failed to file in your office the statement in writing or schedule provided for in the 9th Section of the Act of Congress entitled "An Act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>" <choice><abbr>appd</abbr><expan>approved</expan></choice> <date when="1862-04-16">16 April 1862</date>. You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of the act supplementary to the above act approved <date when="1862-07-12">12th July 1862</date>. The undersigned was a resident of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> on the <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date> still resides therein and had been residing therein for a long time previous with the knowledge and consent of the said <persName>Jesse D. Bright</persName>.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>Remark</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><persName>Fatima Milton</persName></cell>
                            <cell>46</cell>
                            <cell>female</cell>
                            <cell>dark brown 5 ft 6 inches 5 ft 6 inches high</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Fatima Milton</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                        <signed>Tho <persName>McNamee</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>                
              
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01077.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><choice><abbr>pd</abbr><expan>paid</expan></choice></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Fatima Milton</persName></ab>
                        <ab>Servant of <persName>Jesse D. Bright</persName></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Certificate Issued <date when="1862-07-23">23 July 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-07-23">23rd July 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 92.</ab>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
                
                    
                    <div2 type="section">
                        <opener><dateline><placeName>Washington City</placeName> <date when="1862-07-23">July 23, 1862</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>The Commissioners satisfied on the testimony of paymaster <persName>B. F. Gallaher</persName> of the truth of the within statement order the same to be so certified to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><persName>Wm R Woodward</persName> clerk</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div2>
            </div1>
           
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01077.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-07-23">July 23</date>.</dateline>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Jesse D. Bright's</persName> servant</ab>
                    <ab><persName>Fatima Milton</persName></ab>
                    <ab><gap reason="illegible" extent="one character" unit="chars" quantity="1"/></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>B. F. Gallaher</persName>. I know servant as having lived with  <persName>Mr Bright</persName> and was understood as his servant. I only know as to one year prior to and on since the <date when="1862-04-16">16 Apl 1862</date></p>                     
                </div2>
                                                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01077.004.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Fatima <choice><orig>Miller</orig><reg>Milton</reg></choice></persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-07-23">July 23</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
        </body>
